<section id="fs-idm333676336" class="questions">
<title>Questions</title>
<exercise id="fs-idm334942400">
<problem id="fs-idm347133232">
<para id="fs-idm344454960"><link class="lo-reference" document="m67867"/>If a retailer purchased inventory in the amount of $680, terms 3/10, n/60, returned $120 of the inventory for a full refund, and received an allowance for $70, how much would the discount be if the retailer remitted payment within the discount window?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm345517328">
<para id="fs-idm340365808">$14.70; $490 × 3%</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm331580016">
<problem id="fs-idm334957024">
<para id="fs-idm332293280"><link class="lo-reference" document="m67867"/>A customer discovers 50% of the total merchandise delivered from the retailer is damaged. The original purchase for all merchandise was $5,950. The customer decides to return 40% of the damaged merchandise for a full refund and keep the remaining 60%. What is the value of the merchandise returned?</para>
