<exercise id="fs-idm335029200">
<problem id="fs-idm337317728">
<para id="fs-idm346034576"><link class="lo-reference" document="m67867"/>What is the difference in reporting requirements for customer-returned merchandise in sellable condition under a perpetual inventory system versus a periodic inventory system?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm333848672">
<para id="fs-idm345091136">Recognizing the return of merchandise to inventory occurs under the perpetual inventory system but not under the periodic inventory system.</para>
</solution>
